## STEP 12 — Create Custom User Model + DONE

Open:

```txt
users/models.py
```

Create:

```python
from django.contrib.auth.models import AbstractUser
from django.db import models

class User(AbstractUser):

    ROLE_CHOICES = (
        ('expert', 'Expert'),
        ('learner', 'Learner'),
    )

    role = models.CharField(max_length=20, choices=ROLE_CHOICES)
```

